<subSubSection pageNumber="292" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="292">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">Note:</emphasis>
Baum (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">Canad. J. Bot.</emphasis>
45: 1850. 1967) rejected 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hitchcock’s">Hitchcock's</normalizedToken>
typification, proposing instead that 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sloane’s">Sloane's</normalizedToken>
cited t. 14, f. 2 (1707) should be the type. However, the material designated as type was evidently original material for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Andropogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nutans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">A. nutans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and so 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hitchcock’s">Hitchcock's</normalizedToken>
choice has priority. Later authors concurring with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hitchcock’s">Hitchcock's</normalizedToken>
choice include Voss (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">Michigan Bot.</emphasis>
11: 31. 1972), McVaugh, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">(Fl. Novo-Galiciana</emphasis>
14: 142. 1983) and Veldkamp (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="292">Taxon</emphasis>
33: 97. 1984).
</paragraph>
